> Antonio Prieto Martin writes:
>> Will open5066 run on uCLinux?
> 
> Most likely, eventually. 
> 
> open5066 aims at minimal bloat and external library dependencies. It
> seems likely the mini libc that is typically used in uCLinux machines
> is sufficient. I know Felix Leitner's diet libc works. 
> 
> Only potential issue is that we use epoll(4), which is officially
> supported on Linux 2.6 kernel series. I do not know if uCLinux can
> use Linux 2.6. In case it can't, somebody would have to put in extra
> effort to support conventional poll or select. 
> 
> CHeers,
